The course focuses on continuing to develop the four skills of reading, speaking, listening and writing on the Proficiency level of English (C2). The activities and tasks based on course materials increase students' vocabulary related to the respective topics, allow them to practice idiomatic and grammatically correct English in different registers, explore the specificities of style and content of various kinds of texts as well as develop the skill of fluent self-expression in different speaking situations. The independent home reading component of the course develops reading skills of English language texts. Home reading is based on a list of suggested reading which broadens students' background knowledge of literature in English. Writing essays and conversation with the instructor on the basis of the books develop students' written and oral skills of self-expression by providing an opportunity to argumentatively discuss various aspects of the readings.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To further develop the four skills of reading, speaking, listening and writing on the Proficiency level of English (C2). To consolidate and enlarge students' vocabulary, develop their ability to analyse and understand various kinds of texts as well as explore and express ideas on diverse topics both in speech and writing. The course is aimed for students majoring in English language and literature.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the student can understand with ease virtually everything heard or read, can summarise information from different spoken and written sources, reconstructing arguments and accounts in a coherent presentation, can express him/herself spontaneously, very fluently and precisely, differentiating finer shades of meaning even in more complex situations. Achieve the Proficiency level of English (C2). Competence is based on required materials from the textbook as well as related additional readings and tasks provided by the instructor.
